PrvS9m0VCRQ.description:
전 세계의 여성들에게 긍정적인 메시지를 전하기 위해 푸마가 전개하는 우먼스 캠페인 
‘She Moves Us’ 한국에서는 가수 선미와 함께 푸마 우먼스 캠페인을 진행하고 있으며,
그녀를 움직이는 가장 큰 에너지는 바로 가장 ‘소중한 가족’과 ‘함께하는 사람들’ 로
이들을 통해 가장 아름다운 순간에 영감을 얻고, 좋은 기운을 나누며 좋은 결과를 얻을 수 있었다는 
캠페인 메시지를 전했다.

선미를 비롯해 푸마의 우먼스 앰배서더 슈퍼모델 위니 할로우(Winnie Harlow)와 
배우, 모델, 활동가인 카라 델레바인(Cara Delevingne) 또한 ‘She Moves Us’라는 주제로 
각 분야의 정상에 오르기 위해 어떤 도전을 하고 인생의 장애물을 극복해 왔는지, 
어디서 영감을 얻고, 누구에게 도움을 받았는지 등 현재의 모습이 되기까지 노력해 온 
일화를 바탕으로 전 세계의 여성들에게 에너제틱한 메시지를 전하고 있다.

#SheMovesUs #나를움직이는힘
#푸마 #PUMA #선미 #SUNMI #푸마우먼 
#카이아플랫폼 #KAIAPLATFORM

cl_CcG5HH7g.title: SHE MOVES US – PARA CADA NOVO COMEÇO, TEM UMA DE NÓS | PUMA
cl_CcG5HH7g.description:
A PUMA Brasil anuncia o lançamento da nova campanha global #SheMovesUs, uma plataforma de comunicação que eleva as mulheres que se movem juntas para alcançar realizações por meio do esporte, da cultura e de seus próprios valores.

Segundo o último levantamento do IBGE feito em 2015, 68% das mulheres no Brasil nunca praticaram esporte. Por isso, para marcar esse lançamento no Brasil, a PUMA reuniu uma produção essencialmente formada por mulheres para a criação do filme “Para cada novo começo tem uma de nós”, que mostra a realidade de como é começar algo novo entre as mulheres e como é importante o apoio inicial na prática esportiva.

gcNBnc-WN10.title: Is Anyone Listening? ft. Sterling Brown and Claude Johnson | PUMA
gcNBnc-WN10.description:
Is Anyone Listening is an honest and raw conversation about racism between Sterling Brown of the Houston Rockets and Claude Johnson, founder of the Black Fives Foundation.

More than 50 years ago, when Tommie Smith raised his fist on the podium of the 1968 Olympic Games, he risked everything to stand up for universal equality. At a time when racism and police brutality against minorities once again dominate the headlines, Sterling and Claude discuss their experiences and hopes for the future

“Is Anyone Listening?”, is a quote by Tommie Smith in which he expressed his disbelief that so many years after his silent protest on the Olympic podium, racism was still an issue around the world.

#PUMA

gyQ1TvG2yYE.title: Behind the most stylish collab in football | PUMA x KidSuper
gyQ1TvG2yYE.description:
Joining forces  with creative collective KidSuper, we launch the PUMA x KidSuper football collection, which is inspired by PUMA’s football heritage and KidSuper founder Colm Dillane’s past football career in Brazil.
 
KidSuper Studios is a creative collective based in Brooklyn, New York, which transforms streetwear and accessories with fresh takes on style, art, music, and sport. The PUMA x KidSuper Studios collaboration is about combining the love, passion and team chemistry of football with the uniqueness, innovation and energy of the art world. 
 
The PUMA KING is an iconic football boot and for this special product, KidSuper teamed up with Spanish International football player Héctor Bellerín to create a truly unique PUMA KING. A close friendship between Colm and Héctor developed from their love of football and fashion, which opened up the possibility of bringing a fresh new take on this all-time classic football boot.

Shop PUMA x KidSuper: https://us.puma.com/en/us/search?q=puma%20x%20kidsuper

m_d7bQV4xeQ.title: Is Anyone Listening? ft. Tommie Smith, Lewis Hamilton, and Thierry Henry | PUMA
m_d7bQV4xeQ.description:
Is Anyone Listening is an honest and raw conversation about racism between three generations of athlete activists. 
 
 More than 50 years ago, when Tommie Smith raised his fist on the podium of the 1968 Olympic Games, he risked everything to stand up for universal equality. At a time when racism and police brutality against minorities once again dominate the headlines, the panel of PUMA athletes talk about their experiences with racism, activism and their hopes for the future. 
 
 “Is Anyone Listening?”, is a quote by Tommie Smith in which he expressed his disbelief that so many years after his silent protest on the Olympic podium, racism was still an issue around the world
